// This file is hand-maintained, not auto-generated. Most types below are
// thin aliases (or Omit<>+override narrowings) over the real backend
// schemas in `./api-generated.ts`, which IS auto-generated by
// `make.py generate-types` and safe to regenerate at any time.
//
// A type here needs an override (rather than a plain alias) when the
// backend schema is looser than what the frontend actually relies on —
// most commonly a bare `string` where the frontend narrows to a literal
// union (e.g. TaskStatus), or a generic dict where the frontend narrows to
// a known shape (e.g. TmdbGenre[] instead of Record<string, unknown>[]).
// It stays a fully hand-written interface (no `components["schemas"]`
// reference at all) when there is no corresponding backend schema — TMDB
// proxy endpoints return raw `dict[str, Any]`, WebSocket payloads aren't
// part of the REST OpenAPI spec, and a few types are frontend-only
// compositions with no single backing endpoint.
//
// After running `make.py generate-types`, diff `api-generated.ts` against
// this file's `Omit<>` overrides — a schema rename or a newly-loosened
// field will show up as a type error here, not a silent drift.

import type { components } from './api-generated'

